cs.DM, cs.FL, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with combinatorial properties of words over a finite alphabet.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper studies minimally repetitive words, which are closely related to the theory of formal languages.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the growth rate of Dejean words, which can be seen as a measure of the complexity of words and thus related to information theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper establishes the exponential growth of the number of Dejean words, which can be seen as a measure of the computational complexity of generating such words.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the growth rate of a certain class of words, which can be seen as a problem in algorithmic analysis.
